30 PASSAGE]:
31 ARTICLE 53. STATE PARTICIPATION IN FEDERAL TAX
32 CREDIT SCHOLARSHIP PROGRAM
33 Chapter 1. State List of Scholarship Granting Organizations
34 Sec. 1. The department is authorized to and shall as early as
35 practicable elect to participate as a covered state in the federal tax
36 credit scholarship program for elementary and secondary
37 education under Section 25F of the Internal Revenue Code.
38 Sec. 2. (a) The department shall identify qualified scholarship
39 granting organizations located in Indiana that meet the
40 requirements set forth in section 4 of this chapter.
41 (b) The department shall accept applications throughout the
42 year from scholarship granting organizations wishing to be
